When reading a package file I get a parse error, the file contains:

---
package img_gfx_std_func_pack_;

   localparam IMG_CLK_GATE_FANOUT = 32;

   function automatic integer img_log2(integer d);
      integer tmp, COUNT;
      tmp  = 1;
      for (integer COUNT = 0; COUNT < 31; COUNT++) begin // N.B. Synopsys requires static loops.
         if (tmp >= d)
           return COUNT;
         tmp = tmp*2;
      end
      // Should never get here, but add return statement to avoid spyglass warning
      return d;
   endfunction : img_log2
endpackage
--

This produces a parse error but the code is valid:

3. Executing Verilog-2005 frontend: img_gfx_std_func_pack_.sv
Parsing SystemVerilog input from img_gfx_std_func_pack_.sv' to AST representation.
img_gfx_std_func_pack_.sv:43: ERROR: syntax error, unexpected TOK_FUNCTION
